  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0daf\u0ddb\u0db1\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0da2\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "There is not enough jet fuel for airplanes",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that there is not enough jet fuel required for the flights arriving and departing from Katunayake and Bandaranaike Airports on a daily basis.",
        "The Minister also mentioned that the currently stored jet fuel is only enough for 10 or 15 days.",
        "The Minister stated this after visiting the storage complex of the Petroleum Legalized Corporation located at the Katunayake Airport premises and carrying out the monitoring activities there.",
        "The Minister requested the Petroleum Corporation to prepare a permanent and formal program for providing jet fuel.",
        "It was revealed that about 13 lakh liters of jet fuel is required for the daily operations of the airport.",
        "The minister also said that with the start of the tourist season in the coming months, about 14 lakh liters will be required daily.",
        "The Minister further said that since the responsibility of continuously supplying this jet fuel requirement has been assigned to the Mineral Oil Corporation, a certificate should be given to the aviation companies about the ability to supply that fuel.",
        "A group of officials including KDS Ruwanchandra, Secretary of the Ministry of Ports, Shipping and Air Services, retired Major General GA Chandrisiri, Chairman of the Airports and Air Services Company, and Dr. Ajith Mendis, Vice President participated in this event."
      ],
